cs.NI, cs.MA, cs.DS, cs.IT, cs.CR

This paper deals with the performance evaluation of a routing protocol in mobile ad-hoc networks (MANETs), which falls under the category of computer networks (cs.NI). The paper specifically focuses on the Destination Sequenced Distance Vector (DSDV) routing protocol, which is a protocol used for routing in MANETs. Therefore, the paper can also be categorized under the sub-category of mobile ad-hoc networks (cs.MA). The paper also discusses the performance metrics for network load, packet delivery fraction, and end-to-end delay, which are related to data structures (cs.DS) and information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the paper evaluates the security of the DSDV protocol, which falls under the category of cryptography and security (cs.CR).
